<HEADLINE>
CONSTRUCTION OF TAIWAN'S FIRST FIREFIGHTER TRAINING CENTER BEGINS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  May 19 (CNA) 05/19/07  19:34:28 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
A groundbreaking ceremony was held Saturday for the construction
of Taiwan's first firefighter training center under the National
Fire Agency (NFA) in Nantou County's Chushan Township.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony was presided over by NFA Director-General Huang Chi-
min, Nantou County Magistrate Lee Chao-chin, and Legislators Tang
Huo-shen, Chen Chih-pin and Lin Yun-sheng.
</P>
<P>
The training center, which will cover about 109 hectares, will be
the largest in Southeast Asia and the third largest in the world
when construction is completed. The construction project,
carrying a price tag of NT$2 billion (US$59.93 million) , is
expected to be completed in about 660 days, according to Huang.
</P>
<P>
Huang said the training center will be equipped with advanced
facilities capable of simulating different kinds of disasters,
such as large-scale fires, earthquakes and chemical disasters.
Tens of thousands of firefighting personnel and volunteer
firefighters will be trained at the center, he added.
</P>
<P>
The center will consist of a multifunctional area, a training
area, and two flood detention pools, as well as 30 hectares of
green area, he said.
</P>
<P>
Lee expressed his gratitude to those who were instrumental in
pushing to have the advanced training center built in Nantou
County, adding that he expects the training center to boost
employment opportunities and the development of local industries
in the county.
</P>
